news.summary: The Labor government in Oslo relied on conservative opposition votes to force through the measure, which will allow the fund to retain stakes in companies including Microsoft Corp., Amazon.com Inc. and other tech giants.  It’s the first time in the wealth fund’s history that Norway has suspended the work of the ethics council.
